node.text:
@3SAEstate presenting this magnificent mansion in Marbella, Spain 🔑🎾🏊🏻‍♂️🏊🏽‍♀️ #MillionaireLifestyle 

This magnificent mansion boasts breathtaking panoramic views over the golf valley out to sea with Africa on the horizon. Built over three floors, the property features a stunning timeless design with ample, open spaces for socializing. As you enter the villa through its grand entrance, you encounter the double-height ceilings providing a glance of the view as soon as you come in the front door. Two steps down reside the spacious living room, extending to the adjoining kitchen with a family dining area, a separate family room, and also the formal dining room which seats 18 guests. This, along with an office, enjoys direct access to the large terraces, pool, and garden areas outside. On the entrance level, you will also find your home cinema room. Furthermore, the property features four large guest suites and an enormous master bedroom suite with a designer fireplace, seating area, and a stunning dressing room.

The exterior area is divided over two levels, the upper level has a large outdoor dining area with an outdoor kitchen and fireplace, another shaded chiringuito area with a separate fireplace, and by the infinity pool an additional lowered seating area with the most spectacular views. There is also a private padel tennis court and a bar area for evening parties. As you walk down the outdoor stairs in the garden you come down to the recreational areas with a large indoor SPA including an infrared sauna, steam room, jacuzzi, gym, and a massage room.

node.text:
💎 @JacobAndCo introduces the Brilliant Art Deco Skeleton White Diamonds, powered by the exclusive @JacobandCo skeletonized caliber JCAM05 manual wound movement with the one-minute flying tourbillon. 

Underlying the sculpted Art Deco details and diamond-set bridges is a fully mechanical movement made of 172 components and with an impressive 72-hour power reserve. This movement is housed inside a 44mm case paved with baguette diamonds.

-
